The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Brawl, gun chase in Tagore hub
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Brawl, gun chase in Tagore hub
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bolpur, July 17: A Visva-Bharati lecturer was beaten up and abused by a group of youths as he was talking to a woman researcher near his house in Santiniketan last evening.        
	Vishal Bhand, in his 30s, is in hospital with serious temple injuries.         
	Police said the lecturer of Shilpa Sadan, the universitys handicrafts centre, had asked the youths why they were standing near his house, prompting them to leave but after hurling abuses.        
	Bhand took out an airgun from his house and chased the youths, a Bolpur police officer said. In the scuffle, one of the youths snatched the gun and beat Bhand with the butt. Another rained blows. The group fled.        
	His injury in the right temple is serious, said Dr Subrata Ganguly at Pearson Memorial Hospital, inside the campus. The woman lodged the police complaint. Birbhum police chief L.N. Meena said the miscreants were being identified. Vice chancellor Rajat Kanta Ray condemned the attack.                                                                                                                                                                         
